messages.content: cd-tuner_negpip-ComfyUI is a custom node that implements two webUI extensions by [hako-mikan](https://github.com/hako-mikan) for ComfyUI.
Which two webUI extensions does cd-tuner_negpip-ComfyUI implement?

cd-tuner_negpip-ComfyUI implements the following two webUI extensions: sd-webui-cd-tuner (https://github.com/hako-mikan/sd-webui-cd-tuner) and sd-webui-negpip (https://github.com/hako-mikan/sd-webui-negpip).
sd-webui-cd-tuner provides the ability to adjust color tone and amount of writing, with only a portion of its features implemented in cd-tuner_negpip-ComfyUI.
sd-webui-negpip allows for the implementation of negative weights in prompts.
How many nodes are added to the loader with cd-tuner_negpip-ComfyUI?
Two nodes are added to the loader with cd-tuner_negpip-ComfyUI.
What should be specified for the start and end of cd-tuner?
For cd-tuner, the start and end should be specified within the range of 0 to 1000 (not in step units due to implementation reasons).
Who is credited for the original implementation of the two extensions used in cd-tuner_negpip-ComfyUI?
[hako-mikan](https://github.com/hako-mikan) is credited for the original implementation of the two extensions used in cd-tuner_negpip-ComfyUI.
